    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> your<strong> cumin seeds </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant, then add the <strong>diced shallot</strong>, your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punjabi-style-dal-makhani-and-spinach-rice-with-sides/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander </strong>roughly,<strong> </strong>including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punjabi-style-dal-makhani-and-spinach-rice-with-sides/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, a pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, the<strong> remaining cumin seeds </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punjabi-style-dal-makhani-and-spinach-rice-with-sides/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Once the shallot has softened, add the <strong>chopped tomato</strong> and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and cook for 3-4 min further or until the tomato is beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>black beans </strong>and<strong> green lentils</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punjabi-style-dal-makhani-and-spinach-rice-with-sides/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min</p><p>Add the<strong> drained black beans</strong> and <strong>green lentils </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften, then mash them roughly</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if it is looking a little dry \u2013 this will help to thicken the sauce!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punjabi-style-dal-makhani-and-spinach-rice-with-sides/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>stock</strong> and your <strong>garam masala</strong> to the pan and bring to the boil</p><p>Cook for 6-8 min further or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Once thickened, remove from the heat and add stir through your <strong>clotted cream</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>Punjabi-style dal makhani</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punjabi-style-dal-makhani-and-spinach-rice-with-sides/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then chop it roughly</p><p>Once the rice is done, stir through the <strong>chopped spinach </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> spinach rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/punjabi-style-dal-makhani-and-spinach-rice-with-sides/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Punjabi-style dal makhani</strong> with the<strong> spinach rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
